<div id="main"> 
  <h1 id="title"> Ken Saro Wiwa </h1>
  <p> The Death Of Nigeria's Democracy </p>
  <figure id="img-div" > <img id="image" src="https://guardian.ng/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/Ken-saro-wiwa.-Photo-The-Guardian-Nigeria-1062x598.jpg" alt="Photo of Ken Saro Wiwa"> <figcaption id="img-caption"> Face of what would have been Nigeria's democracy. </figcaption> </figure>
  <hr>
  <div id="tribute-info"> <h3> Life and Times of Ken Saro Wiwa: </h3>
  <ul>
    <li> <b>1941</b> - Born in Bori, Nigeria </li> <br>
    <li> <b>1962</b> - Obtains a scholarship to study English at the University of Ibadan. </li> <br>
    <li> <b>1977</b> - Lost the election to represent Ogoni in the Constituent Assembly </li> <br>
    <li> <b>1990</b> - Begins devoting time to human rights and environmental causes, in Ogoniland. </li> <br>
    <li> <b>1992</b> - Imprisoned by the Nigerian military government for several months, without trial. </li> <br>
    <li> <b>1994</b> - Rearrested, accused and charged for inciting the murder of four prominent Ogoni chiefs. </li> <br>
    <li> <b>1995</b> - Executed by hanging following a specially convened tribunal's sentence. </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
    <p id="tribute-page"> For more infomation about this great man, checkout his <a id="tribute-link" href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ken_Saro-Wiwa" target="_blank">Wikipedia Entry</a>.</p>
    
    
